<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>sooth to say • soothsay</xh5><p> <i>sooth to say</i>—(arch. or liter.) in reality; in fact: This message has been published by many newspapers, and, <u>sooth to say</u>, it has sobered many a man.</p><p> <i>soothsay—</i>make predictions; foretell future events: Smart people will stop trying to <u>soothsay</u> the future of economics.</p> </entry>
